append(String str): Appends the specified string to the StringBuilder/StringBuffer.

insert(int offset, String str): Inserts the specified string at the specified position.

delete(int start, int end): Deletes the characters from start index to end index - 1.

deleteCharAt(int index): Deletes the character at the specified index.

reverse(): Reverses the characters in the StringBuilder/StringBuffer.

charAt(int index): Returns the character at the specified index.

length(): Returns the length of the StringBuilder/StringBuffer.


Common Methods for StringBuilder and StringBuffer:
toString(): Converts the StringBuilder/StringBuffer to a String.

capacity(): Returns the current capacity of the StringBuilder/StringBuffer.
